    "The separated oil from conventional down-stream process has a high content of trilaurin giving a melting point at 26 °C that may cause technical issues for some feed and food applications.",
    "Lower trilaurin content and melting point can be achieved by acid hydrolysis of BSFL and/or winterization of the oils.",
    "This will allow producers of BSFL to tailor oil properties to various markets (Bogevik et al., 2022).",
    "BSFL oil is dominated by a few fatty acids (mainly 12:0, lauric acid) (Ushakova et al., 2019) which limit its inclusion levels in cold-water aquaculture feeds.",
    "These feeds normally include fish oil and rapeseed oil with a large distribution of fatty acids including polyunsaturated acids."
  ],
